        <item>
            <title>0.8.5</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 15:34:05 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>805</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.8.5</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.8.5</h2>
<p><b>Your tasks now know when they&rsquo;re due.</b> When Jarvis spots a task
with a deadline &mdash; &ldquo;by Friday,&rdquo; &ldquo;end of day,&rdquo; a
date &mdash; it reads that due date and shows how urgent it is. Overdue and
due-today tasks stand out; things due later sit lower.</p>
<p>Your &ldquo;Needs you&rdquo; list is now sorted by urgency, so the most
time-sensitive task is always on top. Each task row and its detail show a due
badge with the exact date, and VoiceOver reads it aloud. Your sources &mdash;
Slack, Gmail, and Telegram &mdash; are unchanged.</p>
]]></description>
