        <item>
            <title>0.8.4</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 15:22:54 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>804</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.8.4</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.8.4</h2>
<p><b>Telegram sync is more reliable.</b> Telegram would often show
&ldquo;Couldn&rsquo;t sync&rdquo; and ask you to retry &mdash; sometimes over and
over. That&rsquo;s fixed: a normal &ldquo;nothing new to load&rdquo; signal from
Telegram was being mistaken for an error. Telegram now syncs cleanly without the
repeated retries.</p>
<p>Real problems (being rate-limited or offline) still show a retry prompt, just
as before. Your other sources &mdash; Slack and Gmail &mdash; are unchanged.</p>
]]></description>
