        <item>
            <title>0.8.3</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 12:55:37 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>803</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.8.3</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.8.3</h2>
<p><b>Granola sync has been removed.</b> Jarvis records and summarizes your
meetings on its own now, so the separate Granola connection is no longer
needed. If you had connected Granola, it simply disappears from your
sources — there's nothing you need to do.</p>
<p>Any sign-in tokens Granola left behind are cleaned off your Mac
automatically the next time Jarvis launches. Your other sources — Slack,
Gmail, and Telegram — are unchanged.</p>
]]></description>
